WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
You

2
00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:16.560
Crow man

3
00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:24.700
Give it a second, maybe he's taking it out to surrender

4
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.000
He's the anti-heroic, Ron!

5
00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
I don't understand!

6
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
He's only one man!

7
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
With the power of a thousand crows.

8
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Oh!

9
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Good luck!

10
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Crows and owls have always been at war.

11
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:49.000
But why do you care? What's the point?

12
00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:51.000
Here's two.

13
00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Cool!

14
00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
Hey, Morty!

15
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Hey, man! Good to see you!

16
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
You're, like, looking, like, into crows, still.

17
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Oh, uh, two crows. You remember Morty? Morty, two crows?

18
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.000
It's good to see you, but you'd give me more of a heads-up.

19
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.000
Well, I was just in the neighborhood. It wasn't like...

20
00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.000
It's just that the battle for crows is kind of never-ending.

21
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.000
Huh. Right. A little pointless then, right?

22
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:25.000
That came out wrong. Sounded judgy.

23
00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.000
Okay. Looks like...

24
00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.000
Looks like they're leading you to a thing.

25
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Take care, Morty. You two...

26
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
You two... I'm doing good, by the way.

27
00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:39.000
Oh, my dad was gonna eat that yogurt he left in the fridge, but I told him...

28
00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:26.000
I'm looking for crow scare.

29
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:32.000
The scarecrow? The evil scarecrow? Come on. Whoever gives them up first lives.

30
00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:34.000
Fine. I can kill an extra asshole.

31
00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Helped me get my steps in.

32
00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Rick!

33
00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:53.000
Morty?

34
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.000
What?

35
00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:59.000
Morty, why are you now like 40?

36
00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.000
That's how long it's been, Rick.

37
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:03.000
I guess we can have a drink together then.

38
00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:05.000
Do you have a rum and coke?

39
00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:06.000
What are you, 20?

40
00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Oh, bless your heart.

41
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Time be going by, don't you?

42
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:13.000
That's your reaction to finding out you wasted your entire life?

43
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:14.000
I feel okay.

44
00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Well, what about me?

45
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.000
Whoa. Excuse us, boys. You don't want to be here for this.

46
00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.000
I thought if I gave you enough space, you'd outgrow this phase.

47
00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:25.000
Here's your drink, poser.

48
00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:29.000
Dad got sick, you know. Stage 4. You would've loved it.

49
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.000
Summer's a nurse. Well, pretty much a nurse. She married a junkie.

50
00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:37.000
Rick, come home while we still got a little time.

51
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.000
Morty, what we had wasn't healthy.

52
00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:43.000
And this is? You've had a thousand adventures with these crows. When are you gonna kill their big bad?

53
00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.000
First off, the will they kill they is everything to my guys.

54
00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.000
And second, fuck you for trying to undermine my happiness.

55
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.000
This may be the last time you ever lay eyes on me.

56
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:52.000
I hope that's not true, Morty.

57
00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Because you look like shit, and this is not how I want to remember you.

58
00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:14.000
Now that I have his two crows, nothing will stop me from eliminating Crow Rick.

59
00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:18.000
Don't defend him to me. I don't even get what you see in him.

60
00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.000
You're right. We should be enjoying the time we have together.

61
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:25.000
Crow Rick! Oh, I know what this must look like, but...

62
00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:30.000
It looks like my arch nemesis Crow scare and my sidekicks planning adventures together.

63
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:35.000
You are hardly the victim here. I was adventuring with these two crows before you ever came along.

64
00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.000
What do you mean using me as a rebound?

65
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:45.000
You feel like I was using you as a rebound too?

66
00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:48.000
Well, shit. This lost all meaning.

67
00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:53.000
I guess it could have been worse. At least adventuring was just a metaphor for romantic partnership, so it's not a real breakup.

68
00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:57.000
Speak for yourself. We immensely enjoy each other's bodies.

69
00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:58.000
What? Ugh, no!

70
00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.000
Sounds like the man's asking for proof. Let's show him, fellas!

71
00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:04.000
I asked for zero proof! Zero proof!

72
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:13.000
I'm giving you free will.

73
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:14.000
Yah!

74
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.000
Submit to Crow Horse!

75
00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:20.000
Whoops.

76
00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:24.000
Rick?

77
00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.000
Wubba lubba dub dub! I'm back, pal!

78
00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:27.000
Morty, who's at the door?

79
00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.000
Wait a minute. I thought you died gruesomely. What the hell's going on here?

80
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.000
See, the thing is...

81
00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:35.000
Can you please make Morty 14 again, Dad? This is ridiculous.

82
00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Okay, look, I may have used an aging serum to kind of emotionally blackmail you a little.

83
00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:43.000
I kind of figured, and I totally get it, Morty. I'm done with the two crows.

84
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.000
They were super clingy, and I'm ready to make this work.

85
00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.000
Let's just hit the reset button.

86
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:51.000
Honey, not a reset, okay? Tell your grandpa that you're worthy of his respect,

87
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.000
and you want to be treated differently from now on.

88
00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
I refuse to do that. I'm desperate to get back together.

89
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Just like his old man.

90
00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.000
Don't worry, honey. That's just Morty's middle age talking.

91
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
He'll be less codependent once we get more of his life in front of him again.

92
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:05.000
Uh, I'd like him to stay 40 so he can keep buying my friend's Molly.

93
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:08.000
I'd rather throw my Voto Way than usage his Vortiflod system.

94
00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:11.000
Can we make our first adventure fixing this? I keep thinking about lawn care.

95
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:14.000
Okay, buddy. Who sold you this shitty aging serum? What did he look like?

96
00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.000
Just like you. I got it from the Citadel.

97
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:21.000
Hot damn. Hitting the ground running with a Citadel episode. See you later, Master Baters.

98
00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Hi, I'm Citadel's new mascot, Andy, because this place wouldn't be home without Rick's Andy Morty.

99
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:33.000
Dumb.

100
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:34.000
Ooh, what happened to this place?

101
00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.000
There's a Morty president now.

102
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.000
Oh, that's cute. They rebuilt. They made it nicer.

103
00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:39.000
They made it Glendale.

104
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.000
God damn you, or Cantankerous.

105
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:42.000
Even pooping hurts now.

106
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:44.000
Yeah, well, this place is gonna fix you right up.

107
00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
Okay, so we've got a standard Morty that's been aged to 40.

108
00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:49.000
Can you reverse it?

109
00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:53.000
Well, if you look at it like a bone, what we can do is break his age in two places,

110
00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.000
remove the middle, and graft its ends back together.

111
00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.000
That sounds really violent.

112
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.000
It's not a literal bone, Morty.

113
00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:02.000
Oh, okay. Brace yourself. The process does also break every bone in your body.

114
00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.000
Wait!

115
00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:04.000
Ooh!

116
00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.000
Ow!

117
00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:07.000
I like crayons. Girls are gross.

118
00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
I think I feel like myself again.

119
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:15.000
You look a little weird. Your skin's all pink like a baby mouse.

120
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.000
Is that normal?

121
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:17.000
Probably.

122
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
Sign here for storage or disposal of the 26 years we removed.

123
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:22.000
Wait, what? I ain't paying to store 26 years.

124
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:23.000
Well, then you're taking it with you.

125
00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:27.000
I'm almost ready to sell out.

126
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.000
All right, what's disposal cost?

127
00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:32.000
So something unfair is happening.

128
00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
There's no escape. No escape. Let me help you. This is not a good look.

129
00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:37.000
Oh, boy.

130
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:38.000
Hey, they shot me.

131
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.000
You are seriously hurting the Citadel experience.

132
00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:41.000
Listen to me.

133
00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.000
Drop the gun.

134
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:44.000
Get this coming for us all. And the Citadel is a weapon of master's...

135
00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.000
Woof. You're about to get suspended with pay.

136
00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.000
Come on, Morty. Let's get out of here before this gets political.

137
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Uh, was I influential?

138
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:58.000
Yeah, you were influential. You had like seven... seven blogs. Tight.

139
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.000
Too late.

140
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:04.000
Rick C-137, President Morty requests you join him for dinner.

141
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.000
Whoa! Seriously?

142
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
You know I destroyed this place. You've been pardoned for that, sir.

143
00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.000
Rick, let's have dinner with the Morty President.

144
00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:14.000
Morty, the idea was to get back to Simple Adventures. The Citadel runs on cannon.

145
00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:17.000
Okay. I guess things really are just going right back to how they were.

146
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:21.000
Fine. I could eat. But the second he reveals he's evil, we're gone.

147
00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:27.000
I don't know. Tastes pretty good.

148
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:30.000
Okay, let me know if you start feeling poisoning. Good to have you back, buddy.

149
00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.000
Sorry I'm late. Never really ends around here.

150
00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:37.000
Look at this, Morty. They really did make a you the President.

151
00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:40.000
And I hate them every day for it. But wow, Rick C-137.

152
00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:45.000
Now that's a guy to move your schedule around for. Not here to blow the place up again, I hope.

153
00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
Not unless you try to keep me here.

154
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:52.000
Geez, wouldn't dream of it. But it's amazing you dropped by because I was eventually going to hunt you down.

155
00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:54.000
There's the reveal. Let's dance.

156
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.000
Geez. Rick, come on, man. The guy got elected President by Rick's and Morty's. He's being really nice.

157
00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:00.000
All politicians are nice.

158
00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:03.000
He's a hot bag of peanuts, isn't he? We've been through a lot and he does not like...

159
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:05.000
Serialized drama.

160
00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:07.000
Right. No drama. Keep it episodic.

161
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.000
Rick's never looked back. Waste of a legend in his case.

162
00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:12.000
You know he practically built this place?

163
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.000
Wait, what?

164
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:14.000
And now you're running it squeaky clean, right?

165
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:18.000
That's why you got Deformed Morty's coming up through the sewer lines talking about hope and change?

166
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:22.000
Fair enough. Good clap back, Rick. What's the deal with that, Mr. P?

167
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:25.000
I got a little project going on. Required some hands-on labor.

168
00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:29.000
It would require less if you were willing to tell me how one might bring down the central finite curve.

169
00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:31.000
Alright, time to go, Morty.

170
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:32.000
I want to know what he's talking about.

171
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.000
Yeah, you've come all this way. Can you give me ten more seconds?

172
00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.000
Literally ten because now it would be six.

173
00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
Oh, I'm fine with that. Make it two. One.

174
00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
Like I said, it would have been a big help for you to tell me, but I should have everything I need from you now.

175
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.000
You just make sure.

176
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.000
You can't scan an entire brain over appetizers.

177
00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:53.000
Most of yours got scanned a long time ago. You probably don't remember.

178
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:58.000
Check out season one, episode nine, Rick heads. Excel. See our evil Rick.

179
00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:02.000
We kicked his ass. Evil Rick. I love it. Smartest man in the universe.

180
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:05.000
With an ego so big, you can just grab it like a joystick.

181
00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:09.000
Looks complete. I was afraid I'd have to kill every Rick on the Citadel to get what I needed.

182
00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:14.000
You asshole! I vouched for you! He only came here because I asked him to! I'm sorry, Rick.

183
00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:17.000
That apology and a screwdriver in my hand would be worth a screwdriver.

184
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:23.000
You sell out Morty's kill me. I'd hate you more than the Rick's you worship if there was any point, but you can't help it.

185
00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:26.000
You were bred for it. Want to see?

186
00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:33.000
You already know Rogue Rick's used Morty's to hide themselves from the Citadel.

187
00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:37.000
But you might not know it worked so well that the Citadel became its own Morty market.

188
00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:41.000
And I'm sure you don't know how far they've gone to help supply meat demand.

189
00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:46.000
Sure, Rick's could scour infinity for naturally occurring grandsons, but why bother?

190
00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:49.000
So much work. Such an admission of need.

191
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:52.000
There aren't infinite versions of our grandfather Morty.

192
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:55.000
He's an infinite smear of one shitty old man.

193
00:10:55.000 --> 00:11:00.000
And he's attached to us infinitely through his weakness and our forgiveness.

194
00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
This is why we're with him. This is why we're alive.

195
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:11.000
What the fuck? Rick, say this isn't true!

196
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:12.000
It isn't the whole truth.

197
00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:13.000
Liar!

198
00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:14.000
It's complicated.

199
00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:15.000
I'm not busy.

200
00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:19.000
Okay, Morty, remember when I said all I need was your apology and a screwdriver in my hand?

201
00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.000
Well, I forgot I literally have a screwdriver in my hand.

202
00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:23.000
I mean, to do it, I'm basically Inspector Gadget.

203
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.000
Uh-oh.

204
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:28.000
It's okay. He's free to go.

205
00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:31.000
He's the Rickest Rick. We'll never see him again.

206
00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:36.000
Morty, when you came here for that serum, did you refill this gun?

207
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.000
Yeah.

208
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.000
Holy shit!

209
00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:45.000
I only know one man that ever hacked my portal gun, and it turned out it was Evil You.

210
00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:47.000
Yay! He's all caught up.

211
00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:50.000
Wait, hold it! Hold it!

212
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:53.000
Who's that?

213
00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:54.000
Time for big boy.

214
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.000
Does he like it?

215
00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:01.000
It's a metaphor for capitalism, Morty. What do you think?

216
00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:02.000
Oh!

217
00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:20.000
Yoink.

218
00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.000
You can't outrun your past, Rick.

219
00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:25.000
Did you think my force field would be down the second time?

220
00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:28.000
I was expressing disapproval of your dialogue.

221
00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.000
Disapprove all you want.

222
00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:33.000
Tonight, the quality of dialogue stops mattering.

223
00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:37.000
Tonight, I do that thing I want to do with the curve thing.

224
00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:00.000
Fuck you. The drug company's paid for me to say every word.

225
00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:02.000
I have millions of dollars, and I don't care if you lose it.

226
00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:05.000
Oh, God! Oh, fuck no! Oh, fuck!

227
00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:08.000
And I'd just like to say that prescription drugs are great, and you should buy them now.

228
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.000
What's happening, Rick?

229
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:12.000
He hacked the entire city's portal supply. Come on.

230
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.000
There still might be one way out of here.

231
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.000
Now's the bottom.

232
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:23.000
What are you thinking? You need it from your brain.

233
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:25.000
I assume schematics for the Citadel's dimensional drive.

234
00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:28.000
If he's going to use it to blow the curve, we do not want to be here.

235
00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:29.000
What is the central finite curve?

236
00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:31.000
Q&A after our survival.

237
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:35.000
Hopefully we can snack some untainted fluid at the source and get the fuck out of here.

238
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.000
Or not.

239
00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:42.000
Wow, I thought my capitalism metaphor was on the nose.

240
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:46.000
So did you help build the Citadel?

241
00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:47.000
